1.The side meeting examined multicast requirements for AI data center workloads, highlighting use cases such as Mixture of Experts token dispatch, all-reduce broadcast, and model distribution. 
2.Participants identified key needs including bidirectional feedback for reliability, dynamic group membership with minimal signaling, and scalability to thousands of GPUs. 
3.BIER was recognized as a promising foundation due to its stateless nature, though gaps remain in reliability mechanisms and bitstring scalability. Proposals included in-network ACK aggregation and source-driven BIER optimization to eliminate receiver joins. Alternatively we could also consider building a new set of AI specific multicast protocols. 
4.Coordination with other SDO's, such as the UEC (Ultra Ethernet Consortium), was discussed. The discussion in the meeting emphasized the need for quantitative performance data to drive adoption and agreed to continue discussions on the mcast4ai mailing list.
